### 8. Key Patterns & Conventions

**INV-2:** Non-bypassable brickwall limiter on master (threshold=-1dBFS, ratio=20:1)

**INV-3:** Zero-allocation convention - all SAB views pre-allocated at init, no object creation in render loop

**Module IDs:** Factory functions return objects with unique string IDs (`"lane-123"`, `"clip-abc"`, `"mod-xyz"`)

**BBT:** Bar/beat/tick 1-indexed (musician convention), 480 ticks per beat (MIDI standard)

**SAB Communication:** Lock-free audio-thread ↔ UI-thread via pre-allocated typed views (no atomics for Float32/Float64)

**Type Safety:** Discriminated unions for commands/events (EngineCommand, EngineEvent, SynthVoiceCommand, ParameterTarget)

**Disposal Pattern:** All audio graph objects implement `dispose()` for explicit cleanup

**Testing:** Mock AudioContext/AudioBuffer with `vi.fn()`, test audio node creation/connection, parameter mutation

